316_FL.pdf AtlasIntel]\n| March 14\u201316, 2020\n| 1,100 (RV)\n| \u00b1&nbsp;3.0%\n| {{party shading/Republican}}| '''48%'''\n| 41%\n| 11%\n| \u2013\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [https://st1.uvnimg.com/11/92/701333304b6daa2b6b01e98571db/univisionpolling-march-florida-statewide-final.pdf Univision]\n| March 6\u201312, 2020\n| 1,071\n| \u00b1&nbsp;3.0%\n| {{party shading/Republican}}| '''49%'''\n| 42%\n| \u2013\n| 8%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [https://business.fau.edu/departments/economics/business-economics-polling/bepi-polls/bepi-polls-2020/biden-way-ahead-in-sunshine-state.php Florida Atlantic University]\n| March 5\u20137, 2020\n| 1,216\n| \u00b1&nbsp;2.7%\n| {{party shading/Republican}}| '''53%'''\n| 47%\n| \u2013\n| \u2013\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [https://www.unf.edu/uploadedFiles/aa/coas/porl/Feb20.2020.pdf University of North Florida]\n| Feb 10\u201318, 2020\n| 671 (RV)\n| \u2013\n| '''48%'''\n| '''48%'''\n| \u2013\n| 4%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [https://business.fau.edu/departments/economics/business-economics-polling/bepi-polls/bepi-polls-2020/biden-widening-lead-in-florida-where-trunp-has-fallen-behind.php Florida Atlantic University]\n| Jan 9\u201312, 2020\n| 1,285 (RV)\n| \u00b1&nbsp;2.6%\n| 47%\n| {{party shading/Democratic}}| '''53%'''\n| \u2013\n| \u2013\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [https://www.realclearpolitics.com/docs/2019/Mason_Dixon_FL_December_2019.pdf Mason-Dixon]\n| Dec 11\u201316, 2019\n| 625 (RV)\n| \u00b1&nbsp;4.0%\n| {{party shading/Republican}}| '''49%'''\n| 44%\n| \u2013\n| 7%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [https://github.com/ndcohn/battleground-poll-2019/blob/master/FL110419%20Crosstabs.pdf NYT Upshot/Siena College]\n| Oct 13\u201326, 2019\n| 650 (LV)\n| \u00b1&nbsp;4.4%\n| {{party shading/Republican}}| '''45%'''\n| 44%\n| \u2013\n| \u2013\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [https://business.fau.edu/departments/economics/business-economics-polling/bepi-polls/bepi-polls-2019/warren-cutting-